          "message_id": "27667791-5fe5-4608-b2bc-e2dee85b090a",
          "content": "Perfect! ✅ The backward compatibility is now implemented. Here's what happens:\n\n## Migration Process:\n\n### When you run any delegate command:\n1. **Tries new format** - Attempts to parse status.json with `task_ids` field\n2. **Falls back to old format** - If that fails, parses as old format without `task_ids`\n3. **Auto-generates task IDs** - Creates readable IDs for existing tasks\n4. **Saves migrated format** - Updates status.json with new structure\n\n### Example Migration:\n```bash\n# Before (old format):\n{\n  \"subagents\": {\n    \"abc-123-def\": { \"prompt\": \"Create a snake game\", ... },\n    \"xyz-456-ghi\": { \"prompt\": \"Fix the bug\", ... }\n  },\n  \"last_updated\": \"2024-01-08T13:45:00Z\"\n}\n\n# After (new format):\n{\n  \"subagents\": {\n    \"abc-123-def\": { \"prompt\": \"Create a snake game\", ... },\n    \"xyz-456-ghi\": { \"prompt\": \"Fix the bug\", ... }\n  },\n  \"task_ids\": {\n    \"snake_game_001\": \"abc-123-def\",\n    \"fix_bug_002\": \"xyz-456-ghi\"\n  },\n  \"last_updated\": \"2024-01-08T13:45:00Z\"\n}\n```\n\n## What this fixes:\n✅ **No more errors** - Handles old status.json files gracefully  \n✅ **Automatic migration** - Converts old format to new format seamlessly  \n✅ **Preserves data** - All existing tasks remain accessible  \n✅ **Generates readable IDs** - Creates descriptive IDs for old tasks  \n✅ **One-time process** - Migration happens once, then uses new format  \n\nNow you can run any `/delegate` command and it will automatically migrate your existing tasks to use the new readable ID system!"
